  <slide>
    <title>Cataracts</title>
    <contents>

      <figure style="text-align: center">
        <img src="./images/cataracts.jpg" aria-labelledby="cataracts"/>
        <figcaption id="cataracts">Effects of cataracts include some combination of dulling or yellowing, blurring or dimming, and distortion or ghosting of vision.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h2>Symptoms</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Vision becomes blurry and.or cloudy over time.</li>
        <li>Harder to see things both near and far.</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin-top: 4em"><a href="https://www.piedmonteye.com/blog/cataract-causes-and-treatment/">Image from Piedmont Eye Center</a></p>

    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>Glaucoma</title>
    <contents>

      <figure style="text-align: center">
        <img src="./images/glaucoma.webp" aria-labelledby="glaucoma"/>
        <figcaption id="glaucoma">Effects of glaucoma include some combination of tunnel vision, blackout areas, blurred areas, and missing parts.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h2>Symptoms</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>At first, glaucoma doesn’t usually have any symptoms. That’s why half of people with glaucoma don’t even know they have it.</li>

        <li>Over time, you may slowly lose vision, usually starting with your side (peripheral) vision — especially the part of your vision that’s closest to your nose. Because it happens so slowly, many people can’t tell that their vision is changing at first.</li>

        <li>But as the disease gets worse, you may start to notice that you can’t see things off to the side anymore. Without treatment, glaucoma can eventually cause blindness.</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin-top: 4em"><a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/eye2015244">Image from Nature Eye: A view on glaucoma—are we seeing it clearly?</a></p>

    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>Retinitis Pigmentosa</title>
    <contents>

      <figure style="text-align: center">
        <img src="./images/retinitis-pigmentosa.jpg" aria-labelledby="rp"/>
        <figcaption id="rp">Effects of Retinitis Pigmentosa reduces peripheral vision.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h2>Symptoms</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><em>Early Symptoms:</em> Loss of night vision and side (peripheral) vision.</li>
        <li><em>Later Symptoms:</em> Vision loss and blindness.</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin-top: 4em"><a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/eye2015244">Image from Nature Eye: A view on glaucoma—are we seeing it clearly?</a></p>

